Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Cerro Verde, Buenaventura, Casa Grande

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-25T21:21:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/peru-stocks-atacocha-cerro-verde-buenaventura-casa-grande.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 1.4 percent to 22,242.55. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index declined 2.2 percent to 2,996.77.  Mining stocks dropped after polls showed opposition
presidential candidate Ollanta Humala is gaining ground before
the first round of elections April 10, said Leoncio Altamirano,
a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc producer, dropped 5.1 percent to 1.30 soles.
 Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, fell 4.8 percent to 20 cents. Sociedad
Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan
Copper & Gold Inc., declined 4.1 percent to $46.50. Cia. de
Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest precious-
metals miner, fell 4.1 percent to $43.80. Soc. Minera El Brocal
SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver and zinc producer, dropped 1.8
percent to 53.99 soles.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, rose for a fifth session, adding 3.1
percent to 16.75 soles after sugar advanced in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
